        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 28 at 3:18PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 318 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Manvel, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Pearland, South Park, Minnetex, Manvel, Greater Hobby Area, Arcola,
South Acres / Crestmont Park, Hobby Airport, Golfcrest / Bellfort /
Reveille, Iowa Colony, Fresno, South Belt / Ellington, Brookside
Village, Friendswood, Edgebrook Area, Sienna, Sunnyside, Gulfgate
Riverview / Pine Valley, Clear Lake, and Webster.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
